Title : Karim Samir Lotfy
Text : '''Karim Samir Lotfy El Sayed''' (born 21 April 1989) is an [[Egypt]]ian [[high jump]]er.

In age levels he finished eighth at the [[2005 World Youth Championships in Athletics|2005 World Youth Championships]], won the silver medal at the [[2005 African Junior Championships in Athletics|2005 African Junior Championships]], competed at the [[2006 World Junior Championships in Athletics|2006 World Junior Championships]] and finished fourteenth at the [[2008 World Junior Championships in Athletics|2008 World Junior Championships]].<ref name=bio>{{iaaf name|id=208903}}</ref> In regional competitions he finished seventh at the [[Athletics at the 2007 All-Africa Games – Men's high jump|2007 All-Africa Games]], fifth at the [[Athletics at the 2007 Pan Arab Games – Results|2007 Pan Arab Games]] and fourth at the [[2008 African Championships in Athletics – Men's high jump|2008 African Championships]].

His personal best is 2.25 metres, achieved in June 2008 in [[Eberstadt]].<ref name=bio/> This is the [[List of Egyptian records in athletics|Egyptian record]].

